reviews.text:
This is one of those pairings I never would have thought to try on my own so I'm glad Alfred came up with it for me. For such a simple formula, everything feels balanced and paired together nicely. I'm not the biggest fan of mango but I do enjoy grape vapes. This recipe seems to bring the best elements from each flavor and seals the deal with a splash of peach. I haven't tried the FA Apricot sub yet but I imagine it will likely be just as good.&#xD;
&#xD;
In the end I get a crisp, clean fruit flavor. Light enough on the palate and with enough nuances and subtleties to keep it refreshing as an ADV. Seems to work well as a palate cleanse too for those days when you've been vaping enough bakery juices to put Little Debbie out of business. As a bonus feature, the juice fluoresces when exposed to UV light. Fill a tank and check out that purple shimmer when you're out in the sunlight or hit it with a black-light indoors and watch your tank glow.&#xD;
&#xD;
This is definitely worth a try if you're into simple and clean fruits or if you are a fan of either grape or mango.
